text: Welcome to your dream home on top of Barkley Hill. Stunning panoramic views of the bay, mountains, and the twinkling city lights as far as the eye can see. Primary living space including 3 bedrooms total on main floor including Kitchen, living, dining room and laundry all with zero steps. Primary bedroom has en-suite bathroom, double sinks, soaking tub, and separate shower and walk in closet. 2 additional bedrooms, 2nd living area, bathroom, and access to patio area located on lower level. Two upper decks facing West for for outdoor enjoyment and sunset viewing. Centrally located within minutes to shopping, restaurants, entertainment, and trail systems. Home boasts ample storage and a hidden gem-a wine cellar. Come see this today.

Located in the serene community of Sudden Valley, this fully serviced residential lot boasts a gentle slope up from the road - perfect for a 2 or 3-story home design with the garage down. The property backs onto Sudden Valley Community-owned park land, ensuring permanent greenery. Natural gas lines are conveniently located nearby on Harbor View Drive. With its small size, building a home on this lot will be cost-effective with savings on excavation and foundation costs. The property comes with a survey and topo map, with the added bonus of a filtered Lake Whatcom view. Don't miss out on this opportunity! The adjacent vacant lot at 22 Hillside Place is also up for sale.

You must see this exquisitely remodeled home! Fully permitted, leaving less than a 1/4 of the original build. West side location close to downtown amenities and Canadian border. An acre+ of private, usable land provides a serene space for work or play. The custom design remodel provides functional spaces highlighting main floor living, comfort ans style. Top of the line materials used throughout. Oversized 3 bay garage w/ 4th access door to shop & the large barn provide plenty of room for all your toys and entertaining desires. This well cared for home lives large and will not disappoint. Walk through this home today! See additional remarks for more remodel details. Buyer to verify land use options, permit requirements with the city. No HOA

Welcome home to one of the most magical locations in Whatcom County with an outstanding view of Mt Baker and the sisters. In the highlands of Noon Rd is offered this 5 acres parcel that features an architecturally well designed home. Surrounded by a park like setting with its own spa consisting of a 8 person Sauna, Outdoor shower, deck, cold plunge and wired for a hot tub. Adjacent to the spa is a stone masons fire pit, outdoor dining area, and expansive lawn where it's easy to dream about a future build. In additions there is a framed in container style carport for your adventure rig. Reverse osmosis water filter, great water pressure, and have always had plenty of water for irrigation and household water needs.

First time on the market! This very well cared for single-level home in the highly desirable Fieldstone Loop 55+ Community, has all you need! Three bedrooms, thoughtful floor plan, and a 660sf 2 car garage. You will not feel cramped in this 1, 526 sf home with a lovely patio and vaulted ceilings. Enjoy the fitness center, golfing, nearby dining or join friends at the clubhouse that are all a few minutes from your doorstep. The primary bedroom has an en-suite bathroom with soaker tub, separate shower and a walk-in closet. No need to bring the lawn mower or snow blower; the low HOA's include lawn service and snow removal!

Potential awaits! Located down a private lane off Burk Road, this promising fixer-upper resides on nearly 2 acres of land. This single-story, 2, 348 sqft home features an open, but defined floor plan w/ 3 beds & 3 baths. Primary bedroom is spacious w/ sitting area & large en-suite. Relax or entertain on the expansive dual decks spanning 477 sqft, offering ample space for enjoying the surroundings. A substantial 1, 270 sqft detached garage, complete with a stove, presents endless possibilities for hobbies or storage. Plenty of space for parking. With no restrictive HOA rules, the canvas is yours to personalize & elevate to its full potential. Don't miss out on this chance to invest in your vision & unlock the rewards with a touch of TLC.

Stunning Barkley Home! Boasting over 3, 700 sqft of living space with thoughtful upgrades throughout, 2 decks, a patio, vaulted ceilings, & a 2 bedroom apartment... this home is sure to impress! Primary bedroom with private deck, walk-in closet & 5 piece spa-like bath. Charming 2-bed basement apartment w/ separate entrance, high ceilings, kitchen, full bath & laundry. Has been rented out for last 10 yrs & has helped pay down the mortgage. Shop space w/ separate entrance & utility sink for hobbies & projects. Fully-fenced & lined with trees - backyard is extremely private & adorned with lush landscaping, green space & firepit. One of Bellinghams most sought after neighborhoods... close to Barkley Village, trail system, & parks. Welcome Home!

Large lot with stunning views of the Bay, Mt. Baker and surrounding area. Single wide mobile home with large deck, shop and tool shed. Nice big yard partly fenced. Peaceful community off the beaten path and only one way in and out of the subdivision. It is the third house from the top of the hill. Sold as is.

This custom-built, single-level home has endless views and sunlight! Situated on level acreage with south-facing windows and nature all around. In the spring, the swan and geese will be in the fields to the south, and the occasional eagle will hunt that same field year around and land in one of the many trees that border the property and meandering, blacktopped driveway. The floor plan has formal and informal living and there have been numerous updates (including a brand new roof). There is a large 3-car attached garage that has the central vac and Gentran system, and then there is the very large 3-bay shop that has a 15' RV door and stall, plus more covered storage, a garden shed, and a goat pen, along with a fenced 32 x 32 garden area.

Nestled one block from the beach, this fully rejuvenated 3-bed, 2-bath home is located in the highly sought-after Neptune Beach neighborhood! Nicely refreshed with a gorgeous open kitchen, and custom touches throughout. Inviting private deck invites outdoor relaxation with a partial Ocean view. Spectacular & Sandy Neptune Beach has three separate accesses (just steps away) Private backyard oasis creates a sense of luxury. There is a nicely finished shed that could be an office, person cave, workout room etc. Title has been eliminated on the manufactured home.

This beautifully designed home features marine views, privacy & stellar indoor/outdoor flow. The home & additional two-story apartment have been remodeled & are light, bright and gorgeous. The main home features two bedrooms plus loft style media room w/ walk-in closet, full bath, gourmet kitchen, & excellent main floor open concept that creates a functional flow opening onto several decks. The two-story apartment; main floor bright & airy with vaulted ceilings, new kitchen, flooring, paint & bath w/ jacuzzi style tub and private deck. Lower level has a great room, half-bath + walk-out to level yard. This property consists of 3 lots with rock face wall in back, level yard and stream. Homeownership incl. boat launch, beach & swimming lake.
nearby_schools: Lummi Elementary School, Lummi High School, Ferndale School District

text: Beautiful home in the heart of Lynden on a creek front lot with a separate great shop too! Sunshine pours into this kitchen! It has stainless steel appliances, granite countertops & plenty of storage. 4 spacious bedrooms (2 are en-suites) with the primary bedroom and en-suite on the lower level with a private, separate entrance into the home. Large walk in closet, as well as a family room with cozy gas fireplace. Living room has gas fireplace & there is fresh paint & carpets throughout the home, as well as Central A/C! The spacious back yard offers a tranquil lifestyle with a babbling creek, large deck, room to move & is great for outdoor entertaining! Close to schools, parks, walking trails, shopping & Bender Fields. Welcome Home!

This spacious home has been loved by the seller since it was brand new...and now it is your turn to enjoy it! The rooms are spacious and it is on one level. Over the years, they added an atrium-type family room with a bar and rec room with cedar siding inside, large skylights, and floor-to-ceiling windows that look out to the manicured landscaping. The appliances have been updated over the years and there is plenty of cabinet and counter storage space as well as a pantry. The living room looks to the east and has a wonderful view over the church parking lot to take in the sunrises each morning. There is a heated shop and a garden shed in the fully fenced rear yard, as well as an attached, oversized 2-vehicle garage.

Check out this gorgeous new home in Whispering Meadows! It's on a big lot and has 4 bedrooms, 2.25 bathrooms, and 1, 953 square feet. The kitchen has a spacious L-shaped countertop, a walk-in pantry, and stainless steel appliances. The dining room has a sliding door that leads to a covered deck and an awesome backyard for entertaining. The primary bedroom has an ensuite bathroom with a double vanity, quartz countertops, and a tile shower. Plus, there's a huge walk-in closet! The 4th bedroom over the garage could also be used as a bonus room. This home also comes equipped with solar panels to help cut down on those electricity bills.

Located in the serene community of Sudden Valley, this fully serviced residential lot boasts a gentle slope up from the road - perfect for a 2 or 3-story home design with the garage down. The property backs onto Sudden Valley Community-owned park land, ensuring permanent greenery. Natural gas lines are conveniently located nearby on Harbor View Drive. With its small size, building a home on this lot will be cost-effective with savings on excavation and foundation costs. The property comes with a survey and topo map, with the added bonus of a filtered Lake Whatcom view. Don't miss out on this opportunity! The adjacent vacant lot at 20 Hillside Place is also up for sale.

Living at Sunrise Condominiums is quite the lifestyle with all that it has to offer! Pickleball, tennis, weight and fitness room, racquetball, a sauna, a swimming pool, and a hot tub, too! This is a privately situated end unit that has been completely remodeled and has an open floor plan with hickory floors and amazing architectural features! The floor plan is open and the kitchen is AMAZING with quartz counters and cherry cabinets. The living room has French doors that open onto the deck which is incredibly private but looks out to the pickleball court (great entertainment)! The primary suite has a very large walk-in closet and a tiled 3/4 bath. This is your golden opportunity as these larger units do not come available often.

Charming and updated historic 1910 Craftsman in the Lettered Streets! Owned by only one family for over 100 years with the original character retained. This home is located close to parks, a short bike ride or stroll downtown! Inviting features include 9 ft+ ceilings, reskimmed plaster walls and ceilings, original built-in's, millwork, refinished hardwood flooring, reglazed clawfoot tub, and window bench seating. The kitchen is complete with a breakfast nook plus retro-style refrigerator. All new period light fixtures from Rejuvenation. Unfinished, workshop-style basement, with washer and dryer (approx. 288 sq. ft). Fenced, grassy backyard. Off-street parking in driveway + street parking. Detached garage with alley access or possible ADU?

Chuckanut Mntn views from this comfortable 4bed home on Samish Hill. Enter into the open entry, looking through family room w/ vaulted ceilings, skylights, 2 sided fireplace & out to deck. Large kitchen w/ induction stove & island seating, opens to family room. Formal dining & living room. Maple hardwood throughout & into main floor primary bedroom w/ spacious ADA compliant ensuite bathroom. Second bedroom on main has french doors. Daylight basement feels open & very bright w/ a third living space including fireplace, storage room, laundry & 2 bedrooms. Parkhurst neighborhood is a walker's dream of wide streets, sidewalks, views, & close to Lake Padden. Newer roof/exterior paint. Chair lifts available for stairs. Quiet cul de sac.

34 ft slip in the best marina in the PNW. Ideal port tie, bow in location steps from main walkway and gated entrance. Plenty of well maintained dock carts make for easy provisioning. Unit includes 30 amp power, WiFi and spacious dock box plus keyless access to the laundry room, mail room, restrooms, shower facilities, and reduced price fuel dock. Remodeled cafe/store, and member only patio just outside the gate. Excellent management and clean facilities. Perfect starting point for cruising the San Juans, Gulf Islands, BC Coast, and all the Salish Sea has to offer. World class crabbing, shrimping, and fishing opportunities nearby as well. Slip allows for 34 ft vessel with 13 ft beam. Owner financing available.

Bellingham's most sought-after areas, boasting classic homes nestled alongside Broadway Park. Meticulously maintained two story w/basement. Main level primary suite added in 2013 w/wall of built-in closets, bay window, bath w/dual sinks, tiled shower & radiant floor heating. 3 bd & full bath upstairs. Kitchen w/breakfast nook, formal dining rm both w/wood flrs. Living rm w/tiled FP & lrg picture windows looking at the park. Den/office space. Dt dbl garage off alley. Easy care yard. Tankless water heater, gas force air. Here is your chance.

Welcome to your new home in the serene Cordata neighborhood! This immaculate 2 bed, 2 bath single level, detached condo offers comfortable living in a 55+ community. Solid surface counters and SS appliances make the kitchen the perfect retreat for chefs of all levels! Cozy up in the living room with the gas fireplace and your views overlooking the quiet walking path and mature landscaping. Water, sewer, lawn care, roof and exterior maintenance is all covered by your HOA fee! The neighborhood offers walking trails and a club house with regular organized activities. This is a must see if you are looking to move towards a quieter and less maintenance lifestyle!

Very nice home on 21 acres. This 2895 square foot, 4 bedroom home was remodeled 4 years ago with granite countertops and Thermador appliances. A detached 2 car garage with a wood working shop. A separate garden shed. The red outbuilding had a workshop and an indoor, insulated gun range with an automatic target retriever. Next to this is a very secure locking vault. Also storage in the back for equipment. The outbuilding behind is for more equipment storage. The next outbuilding is heated with a bathroom, storage area and stall for cows. There is a pasture. Then you will have to walk to the back south end of the property where there is a heated cabin with a bathroom and kitchen overlooking a pond with a dock. An awesome property to see.

Don't miss this one-level, 2 bed/1.75 bath, 1268 sqft condo in a great Bellingham location! Bath off primary bedroom w/soaker tub, low-threshold shower & walk-in closet. Large living room w/gas fireplace w/french doors to new composite rear deck w/new power coated aluminum railings & gate. Dining area off kitchen w/Marmoleum floor covering. Newer high-efficiency, natural gas forced-air furnace w/AC. Attached one-car garage w/storage space. Gated entry & secure mailboxes. Newer roof & exterior paint. All appliances & window coverings inc. Plumbed for central vac. Exterior maintenance, landscaping, water/sewer & HOA reserve contribution included in monthly dues. Great location near shopping, recreation center, parks trails & I-5 access.

Discover the allure of single-level living at this charming 3-bedroom, 2 bathroom home on Kramer Lane. Nestled at the end of the street in a peaceful culdesac, this residence boasts a fully fenced yard for privacy and outdoor enjoyment. Home features include radiant floors, skylights, vaulted ceilings, new interior paint & gas fireplace. Large 2 car garage and driveway provide plenty of off street parking. With a well-maintained interior that's flooded with natural light this home offers comfort and convenience in a serene setting. Close to amenities, schools, and parks, this property presents an ideal opportunity for those seeking a tranquil lifestyle in the heart of Bellingham.

Welcome home! Turn key opportunity for charming country living. This spacious 3bd/2bath home boasts natural light throughout & two fireplaces to keep cozy year around. It features beautiful reclaimed wood accents from a 100 year old barn that once stood on the property. Like to entertain? Well, you wont have a problem as this home has large open living spaces to do just that. Fully fenced 1.2 acres complete with chicken coop, garden beds, mature trees, picturesque swings, firepit, hot tub, all coupled with incredible views surrounding. Just in time for planting season, start your very own mini farm without having to invest thousands on infrastructure. Close to town & amenities, but far enough out to catch a quiet country breeze. Come & See!

Panoramic views from every room of this custom-built South Hill home. Street level entry to main living space, gourmet kitchen & 1/2 bath. Second level dedicated to spacious master suite w/adjoining den w/wet bar, expansive bath w/walk in shower & deep soaking tub, huge closet & laundry room. Third level 2 bedrooms, bath & large heated storage. Covered decks all levels. Well-designed plan w/elevator! Fourth level shop/work-out room. Terraced gardens, 2-car garage + off-street parking.

Introducing Lynden's iconic Victorian home, a true gem in the real estate market! This stunning property underwent a complete remodel in 2006 with no expense spared. Boasting 4 bedrooms, 3.25 bathrooms, and over 3, 000 SF of living space, it offers a perfect blend of modern amenities and timeless charm. The kitchen is equipped with top-of-the-line appliances, while the hardwood floors exude elegance throughout. Upstairs, you'll discover 3 bedrooms, including the primary bedroom with vaulted ceilings, a luxurious bathroom with heated floors, and the unique feature of a copper tower you can climb into. Additionally, the property includes a detached garage with an ADU above. Too many features to list. Come see for yourself!

This well-maintained Tahoe park model sits on a property backing up to beautifully lush greenspace. Sit on the covered porch and enjoy the weather or sit around the campfire. Inside, the bedroom is in back for privacy, and the open living space is great for entertaining. An add-a-room is included and makes for a perfect flex room! A shed also sits on the property for additional storage. The Glen is zoned recreational for 120 days of use out of the year and has all the amenities you could want, including 2 pools, hot tub, tennis court, library, laundry mat, 2 clubhouses, 24 hr security, gated entry, & play areas.

Discover the perfect blend of comfort and convenience in this 1, 250 square foot, one-level standalone condo, nestled in the heart of the vibrant 55+ community of the Village in the Cordata neighborhood. This charming home boasts 2 spacious en-suitesone with a walk-in shower and another with a standing tub. Freshly updated with new interior paint and carpet, the home is ready to move into, with a 2-car garage plus workbench, welcoming patio, and a kitchen with ample storage and a breakfast nook. The HOA covers exterior upkeep, cable tv, w/s, and landscaping ensuring a worry-free lifestyle. Close to local restaurants, clinics, parks, shopping, medical facilities, & transit. Embrace a lifestyle of convenience and community in this rare find.

For your most discerning clients. This home was designed by a famous architect and built from the finest materials. The result was a masterpiece of design. One level home on a quiet south hill street close to WWU. The third bedroom is currently a library with built in bookshelves. You will find the living area warm and inviting. Very private back yard with both patio and deck. Easy walk to WWU.

Beautifully restored Craftsman, steps from Sunnyland school, pubs, & TJs. Charm abounds w/ bright wood wrapped windows, wood floors, fireplace, & old world trim. You will love the updated kitchen w/ SS appliances & Quartz counters. The full bath has just been refinished w/ tile surround, new vanity, & new tile flooring. Pride of ownership is evident in every detail & meticulous care has been taken to ensure every space is move-in-ready. Home offers main floor living w/ laundry, two baths, primary bedroom, & 2nd bedroom/office on main. Two additional bedrooms upstairs and 500+ SF of storage in the basement. You will love the gardens, patio w/ natural gas BBQ hookup, greenhouse, chicken coop, alley access garage & potential for future ADU.

Rare opportunity! 2132 sqft Rambler w San Juan & Canada views! Sit back & enjoy the Beach, Sound, and Island vibes. Move-in ready so you can live there as-is, collect rent as a great VRBO investment, and live the dream amid other high-value owner-occupied homes. Just relax while you soak in the Brand New Hot Tub while enjoying wonderful San Juan Sunsets from your private beach. This waterfront property is approx 3.48 acres w 97ft +/- of unobstructed waterfront. The remainder of the 3.48 acres is across the street & is a treed/undeveloped area. There is an attached studio/suite w 1 Bed-3/4 Ba and Kitchen & Laundry Rm. New Electric Gate for privacy, fully fenced on beachside with space for added parking, RV Space & 2-car garage. Great space!
nearby_schools: Lummi Elementary School, Lummi High School, Ferndale School District

text: Experience beautiful forest views from the comfort of your living room. This home is well thought out, functional and modern with Quartz countertops, soft close cabinets, roman shades, and great accent lighting round out the kitchen. Spacious great room and fantastic primary bedroom on the main floor. Bonus room, bathroom and 2 bedrooms downstairs complete the home. A flat driveway gives easy access to the 2 car garage. All the Sudden Valley amenities - golf course, community pool, boat launch and lake access make this a great home. A must see.

Rare opportunity to own a home with a view on Marine Drive. Situated on 4 acres of land just minutes from downtown Bellingham, this property offers stunning views of Lummi Island and Canada. This charming home has 3 beds/1.75 bathrooms, 2 flex spaces, large basement with tons of potential, attached garage, hardwoods, a spacious kitchen with stainless steel appliances that convey, and all new interior paint. With plenty of space both inside and out, this property is the ideal retreat for those looking for a peaceful and picturesque setting. Don't miss out on this unique opportunity to own a piece of history in a prime location!

This home is the perfect blend of comfort & charm! An inviting 3 bed, 2.5 bath home, nestled on a spacious corner lot for plenty of extra yard space & featuring a thoughtfully designed open floor plan. Functional kitchen layout w/ sleek granite countertops & stainless-steel appliances. Unwind in the warmth of the gas fireplace, creating a cozy ambiance on cool evenings. Enjoy tranquil mornings w/ a coffee on the covered front porch while you watch the sun rise. Indulge in outdoor living on your covered back deck, w/ a fully-fenced yard. Perfect for hosting summer BBQs! The large attached 2-car garage provides ample space for vehicles & storage. Just minutes from both Lake Whatcom & Barkley Village, this location couldn't be more convenient!

Looking for a great investment property with MIL or ADU potential? Located in Gate 3, this 2900+ sqft home features a FLAT driveway & main level living. Bright open concept with primary bedroom on the main with jack & jill closet shared by second bedroom. Utility room & half bath also on the main floor. Downstairs boasts 2 separate entries, 3 bedrooms, full bath & living area. Each floor is equipped with gas to add a fireplace. New carpet, paint, furnace & range. A little more TLC is needed, but the heavy lifting is done! Fully fenced backyard backs up to Sudden Valley owned green belt. Enjoy amenities including: golf course, community beaches, clubhouse, marina, swimming pool, trails & more! $10k closing cost credit to the Buyer.

Here is a rare discovery to build your dream home on a stunning 0.26 acre lot on the Semiahmoo Community. Having old growth fir trees, and situated in the Carnoustie neighborhood, this lot will provide its new owner with privacy as well as views of Drayton Harbor, Canadian Rockies, and White Rock, BC. Conveniently situated only 10 minutes from the US/Canadian border. Be part of an upscale Semiahmoo gated neighborhood, that offers a private golf club, tennis, fitness club, marina, restaurants, and saltwater beaches. Being only one of two lots in the Carnoustie neighborhood, don't miss out on this opportunity to call this place your forever home.

This stunning Edgemoor home offers breathtaking saltwater vistas, exceptional architectural design, and meticulously curated gardens. Thoughtfully renovated, the residence showcases a gourmet kitchen with high-end appliances, ambient lighting, beautiful cabinetry, and granite surfaces. The luxurious primary suite leads to a secluded patio with panoramic bay views and a custom closet. The spa-inspired ensuite bathroom features a lavish soaking tub, radiant heated floors, and a spacious shower. Set amidst tranquil grounds with charming walkways and a secluded gazebo, this property is a true sanctuary.

5 bedrooms home with 3 bathrooms, 3 living rooms and 2 extra storage room. 3 car garage with 3288 finished sqft home well maintained and has a great view of the hills, daylight basement with separate entrance (if you wanted to rent out the bottom). Kitchen with wood cabinets, breakfast island, kitchen nook, fireplace in living room and back deck, lots of light. Front living room is large and great for entertaining, with formal dining space. Huge living space on the lower level great for a gaming room or 3rd living room or make it a Very Large bedroom. partial Fenced in back yard that is perfect for your garden, dogs or pool!. Large Bpnus room behind lower living room that would make a great gym or media room & smaller storage room.

Charming craftsman home located in the Meridian School District. This property is just shy of an acre & is located on a quiet road making it feel like you are out in the country, but its only minutes to town. When entering the home, you will be met w/ huge windows & lots of natural light. The kitchen is open to the dining room & one of two living rooms. French doors lead to the 2nd living room which includes a beautiful fireplace, views of the private back yard & a door leading out to the multiple back porches. The yard is a dream w/ terraced gardens, fruit trees, tree house, gazebo & a 24X28 detached shop. Evergreen trees on the property line provide lots of privacy. Finishing the basement would add sq. feet. Great place to live!

Gorgeous newer home in the heart of the Reserve at Cordata, South Springs Neighborhood. Attractive 2 level home with primary bedroom on main floor with ensuite & walk-in closet. 2 bedrooms upstairs with a Jack & Jill bathroom & laundry room. 10' ceilings, hard surfaces throughout, gas fireplace, granite kitchen, light & bright with a private back patio. Washer/dryer on both upstairs AND down for your convenience. 2 car garage. Located very close to brand new regional City Park. Close to all City services with central Community Park as well.

Welcome to the heart of Ferndale! This lovely remodeled 3bd 2ba home offers both a family room and a living room, perfect for relaxation and entertainment. The main level features a primary bedroom complete with a walk-in closet and ensuite bath, while the open concept kitchen seamlessly connects to the living areas, facilitating effortless flow throughout the home. A fully fenced yard, featuring a spacious patio ideal for hosting gatherings or simply enjoying the outdoors in privacy. Upstairs, two additional bedrooms and a bathroom await. With updated paint, flooring, appliances and lighting, this move-in-ready home exudes a fresh, and inviting atmosphere. Complete with a 2-car garage, a charming front porch, and adorable appeal.

Totally unique, remodeled, and cared for home in the coveted Columbia neighborhood. Remodeled with modern conveniences while preserving original character. You'll love the proximity to area parks like Elizabeth and Squalicum, and the beautiful Bham waterfront. All knob and tube replaced with Romex, roof, main sewer stack, and main bathroom all completed, with permits, in '14. Additional 1/2 bath ('22), fully finished 330 sf basement ('23), and new exterior paint ('23). Move-in ready with flexible 352 sf heated & insulated garage that can be used as shop, garage or how you see fit. Two ample-sized alley parking spaces & street parking. Fully fenced with covered porch, garden, mature blue/raspberry bushes, fruit trees, & plenty of sunshine.

Escape to your own private sanctuary on 5 serene acres! This meticulously updated Craftsman home offers a harmonious blend of modern comfort and rustic charm. With 3 bedrooms plus a bonus room and a finished walk-out basement, there's ample space for everyone. Enjoy the tranquility of nature from your expansive deck overlooking a picturesque pond, perfect for relaxation or outdoor gatherings. Nestled in a secluded setting on a dead end road, yet conveniently located for easy access to all Bellingham has to offer. Many recent updates include a newly updated kitchen, new roof, composite deck, new exterior paint, new furnace and A/C. Don't miss this opportunity to experience the peaceful retreat you've been dreaming of!

Investor Alert! Seize the opportunity to invest in a prime Bellingham duplex with excellent maintenance and a stellar rental record. Each unit offers 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, complete w/ separate garage space for each unit. Strategically located close to downtown, Trader Joe's and an array of shopping and restaurants, this property promises unparalleled convenience for tenants. The lower unit features lofted ceilings, a fully fenced private yard designed for minimal upkeep, a cozy gas fireplace and A/C. The upper unit delights with a sun-drenched private deck and great city views. Exceptional multi-family investment opportunity in a sought-after location.

Fantastic opportunity to build your dream home in a serene environment with beautiful trees, a seasonal stream, in a park-like setting.The location near Galbraith Mountain is highly sought after and provides easy access to nature trails and recreational activities. Close to building permit ready: The presence of a driveway, power on the property, active septic permit and completion of the wetland delineation are all positive aspects. The inclusion of 1901 sf house plans is a valuable asset, allowing you to envision the design and layout of your future home. The marking of property corners, as well as the house and septic site, ensures clear boundaries and positioning. Close to I-5, Lake Padden and all amenities.

Welcome home! This single level beauty is move in ready and has the perfect open concept layout. Enjoy the fenced back yard and spacious back deck! Conveniently located close to multiple lakes and the beginning of the Mt Baker Highway, this home is the perfect jump off for the outdoor enthusiast!

Spacious 3000+ sq ft home in the beautiful & peaceful Sudden Valley community. Located just over 1 mile off Lake Whatcom Boulevard this custom-built Apex home with a greenbelt backyard is close to all amenities including marina, fitness center, pool & more. Space for everyone including a luxurious primary suite on the upper level with walk-in closets, shower & its own sitting area with gas fireplace to enjoy coffee or a good book. Main level features open kitchen with newer appliances & granite counters. Light-filled living room with 2nd gas fireplace and deck facing the forest. Downstairs features generous sized bedrooms, additional living room with wet bar & guest bathrooms. 2 car garage. All situated on a low-maintenance property!

Welcome to this charming 2-bedroom, 1-bath gem nestled just 5 minutes away from the picturesque Birch Bay! Whether you're a first time home buyer, downsizers, or looking for an investment opportunity, this home checks all the boxes. Don't miss out on the chance to make this delightful property your own. Only 15 mins from I-5 - Tenants currently in the home. All interior photos are prior to tenant.

This home exudes curb appeal and tranquility. A mid century home that blends partial modern updates with potential for the discerning buyer to customize and create their dream residence in the beautiful Edgemoor neighborhood. Expansive kitchen, open living & dining with abundant natural light, overlooks the outdoor deck, patio and the natural backdrop of a lush fenced yard. Large 3-bay, deep garage, with finished, unheated bonus area above. All set on large lot with mature landscape and a circular drive. Feel away from the hustle and bustle with all the convenience of urban living.

Amazing condo in the heart of Bellingham, located close to amenities, entertainment, local farmers market & I-5. This third story condo with elevator access features bright finishes that compliment the natural light that pours through the extra windows throughout this coveted corner unit. Open kitchen and dining space, cozy fireplace in the corner of the living room, an excellent heat source for the main part of the home. Off of the dining room is the balcony that gets nice sun during the day, overlooking the market. The primary BR features a reading nook and full bath. The extra bedroom/office boasts French doors and lots of natural light. This unit has a W/D and plenty of extra storage! Underground parking for your safety.
neighborhoods: Downtown District Bellingham, City Center Bellingham

text: Affordable mid century modern living in Ferndale! One of the classic three bedroom designs found in the Ferndale Terrace/Seamount area with a cool California vib. Beautiful hardwood floors grace the home with vaulted ceilings giving it a wonderful bright open feel. Oversized windows bring all day sun. Newer appliances in the kitchen.
